{
  "text": "Our previous studies have demonstrated that the effects of insulin and amino acids on muscle protein synthesis are additive until maximum rates of protein synthesis are achieved [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Both insulin and amino acids also independently stimulate muscle protein synthesis [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . Fed levels of amino acids promote protein synthesis rates in the muscle to levels similar to that observed in fed animals, even when insulin and glucose are maintained at fasting. Likewise, raising insulin to fed levels, even when amino acids and glucose are maintained at fasting, also increases rates of muscle protein synthesis.",
  "correct_citation": {
